[This is becoming a very instructive event as we watch the Upper East veterinarians struggle to be able to travel from farm to farm to vaccinate their cattle. The FAO data on Ghana shows that Ghanaian cattle are concentrated in the upper half of the country and most densely in the small Upper East Region. Thus the concentration of cases in this area.

To find the North-East Region go to:
http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/africa/ghana_admin_2007.jpg.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1jUt.
- Mod.MHJ]
